Hello again.

Not so many activity happening here : )

First of all, I've found a bug. Program incorrectly detects what
monitor it's window is at. So when I drag window to 550s monitor, I'm
suggested settings for 173P, but dragging it back to 173P displays me
error message, as 550s doesn't support DDC.

I've dug some code, but cannot say, whether this bug is in radeon's
driver xinerama implementation, GTK's gdk_screen_get_monitor_at_window
function or somewhere else.

As temporary solution I just swapped 2 lines in ~/.ddccontrol/monitorlist:
 <monitor filename="pci:01:00.0-1" supported="1" name="Samsung
SyncMaster 173P (DVI)" digital="128"/>
 <monitor filename="pci:01:00.0-0" supported="1" name="VESA standard
monitor" digital="0"/>


