I have just installed and configured ddccontrol under
Mandriva Linux (kernel version 2.6.17-13mdv) on
an AMD dual core.  The video controller is an ATI
Radeon X 1700 FSC (or at least, that's what Windows
said, before I replaced it with Linux); Mandrake says its
from ATI, is VGA compatible, and doesn't seem to
know anything else about it (Unknown device 71c1,
description unkown, module unknown).

The monitor is an LG L1900E; Mandrake seems to
recognize this.

The output from ddccontrol is:

    Gabi (92): LANG=3D LC_All=3D ddccontrol -p -c -d
    ddccontrol version 0.4.2
    Copyright 2004-2005 Oleg I. Vdovikin (oleg@...13...)
    Copyright 2004-2006 Nicolas Boichat (nicolas@...3...)
    This program comes with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY.
    You may redistribute copies of this program under the terms of the
GNU General Public License.

    Probing for available monitors....
    Detected monitors :
    No monitor supporting DDC/CI available.
    If your graphics card need it, please check all the required
kernel modules are loaded (i2c-dev, and your framebuffer driver).

(I'm not too experienced with configuring Linux, so it's quite
possible that I've got something wrong in my Linux
configuration.  I don't have any /dev/i2c devices, for example,
but if I understand your documentation correctly, this shouldn't
be necessary for an ATI Radeon graphics controller.)

